Type: Package
Package: erpm
Title: Exponential Random Partition Models
Version: 0.1.0
Date: 2024-03-13
Authors@R: c(
    person("Marion", "Hoffman", , "marion.hoffman.31@gmail.com", role = c("cre", "aut", "cph"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-0741-7760")),
    person("Alexandra", "Amani", role = "aut")
  )
Description: Simulates and estimates the Exponential Random Partition Model presented 
    in the paper Hoffman, Block, and Snijders, 2023. It can also be used to estimate
    longitudinal partitions, following the model proposed in Hoffman and
    Chabot, 2023. The model is an exponential family distribution on the
    space of partitions (sets of non-overlapping groups) and is called in
    reference to the Exponential Random Graph Models (ERGM) for networks.
